==English==

===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''babiroussa'', from Malay ''babi'' hog + ''rusa'' deer.
===Noun===
'''babiroussa'''
# A large [[hog]]like [[quadruped]], of the [[genus]] ''[[Babyrousa]]'', found in the [[East Indies]], sometimes [[domesticate]]d; the [[Indian]] hog. Its upper [[canine]] teeth or [[tusk]]s are large and recurved.

